    <h2>Data Collection</h2>
    <ol>
        <li><b>User Information</b>: When you create an account via GitHub authentication, we collect information
            necessary to manage your account, such as your GitHub username and email address.</li>
        <li><b>Service Data</b>: We collect data related to your usage of the caipi.ai services, including project data
            and API usage statistics, to enhance service functionality and user experience.</li>
        <li><b>Cookies and Tracking Technologies</b>: We use cookies and similar technologies to track user activity on
            our website and store certain information. This helps us improve our services and personalize your
            experience.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Data Use</h2>
    <ol>
        <li><b>Service Provision</b>: We use the collected data to provide and improve our services, manage user
            accounts, and assist users with project development.</li>
        <li><b>Communication</b>: Your email address is used to communicate important information about your account,
            updates to our services, and respond to your inquiries.</li>
        <li><b>Analytics</b>: We analyze usage data to understand how our services are used and to make improvements.
        </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
    <ol>
        <li><b>Third-Party Services</b>: We may share your data with third-party LLM providers integrated into caipi.ai
            to enable specific functionalities. These providers are required to comply with their own privacy policies
            and acceptable use policies.</li>
        <li><b>Legal Requirements</b>: We may disclose your information if required by law or in response to valid
            requests by public authorities (e.g., a court or government agency).</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Data Protection</h2>
    <ol>
        <li><b>Security Measures</b>: We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your
            data against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.</li>
        <li><b>Data Retention</b>: We retain your data only as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in
            this policy, comply with legal obligations, and resolve disputes. API invocation data is stored for 30 days
            for monitoring purposes.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>User Rights</h2>
    <ol>
        <li><b>Access and Correction</b>: You have the right to access your personal data and request corrections if it
            is inaccurate or incomplete.</li>
        <li><b>Deletion and Restriction</b>: You can request the deletion of your data or restrict its processing under
            certain conditions.</li>
        <li><b>Data Portability</b>: You have the right to obtain a copy of your data in a structured, commonly used,
            and machine-readable format.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>International Data Transfers</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>We ensure that data transfers outside the EU are conducted with adequate levels of protection in accordance
            with GDPR and other applicable data protection laws.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
